- Success rate refers to the percentage of successfully transmitted packets out of the total packets; 
- Retransmission count is the number of times a packet is resent due to transmission failure; 
- Permissions define the allowed actions (e.g., read, write, delete) a user can perform on a specific resource.

sql:
SELECT MAX(size) AS max_packet_size
FROM packets
WHERE device_id = 1;

SELECT packet_type_name
FROM packet_types
WHERE default_retransmission_limit > 3;

SELECT AVG(size) AS average_packet_size
FROM packets
WHERE packet_type_id = 0 AND device_id = 1;
